main event: A white and red oblong object with a diameter of twelve to fifteen feet was observed drifting slowly to the southwest in Live Oak, Florida on April 30, 1955.
interesting points: The object changed color as it passed over the observer., It was described as having an oval shape., The object was not formally observed by designated officials., The report includes incomplete data for analysis., The sighting occurred over a period of 5 minutes and was conducted by a civilian.
